Kept retention as shared-engine behavior rather than a hosted-only rule.

Implementation details:
- trimming runs inside `LocalEngine`
- replay and prefix logic consume the retained frontier in the shared engine
- hosted protocol/status surfaces only report the shared-engine result

Focused proof:
- `cargo test -p transit-core retention`
- `cargo test -p transit-cli --bin transit remote_cli_helpers_cover_core_server_workflows`

Observed result:
- embedded and hosted flows observe the same retained frontier semantics
